{"_id":"absinthelab001","name":"Adrien's Absinthe Laboratory","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Secret distillation laboratory in church basement where Father Adrien produces illegal absinthe. Large cellar adapted for distilling operations with distinctive absinthe smell recognizable to anyone with slightest knowledge of distillation. Heavy trap door connects cellars to catacombs where Adrien passes loads of absinthe to his henchmen. Discovery of this laboratory by little Yvonne led to her murder. Adrien strangled girl unconscious and burned her alive to hide his smuggling operation. Source of priest's wealth used to fund escape to New World.","location":"Church of Saint Pierre basement cellar","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"absinthe001","name":"Adrien's Smuggled Absinthe","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Illegal absinthe distilled by Father Adrien in secret church basement laboratory. Green alcoholic spirit with distinctive smell recognizable to anyone with knowledge of distillation. Adrien passes loads through heavy trap door connecting cellars to catacombs where his henchmen (the Ravens gang) distribute it. Smuggling operation funds Adrien's planned escape to New World. Several broken bottles scattered in Ravens' Hideout in catacombs with strong alcohol scent still present. Adrien chose holy vows to avoid life of struggle but does not shy away from life's pleasures. Accumulating wealth through absinthe trade.","quantity":12,"weight":2,"value":150,"equipped":false,"properties":["Illegal alcohol","Distinctive smell","Smuggled goods","Source of Adrien's wealth","Distributed by Ravens"],"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"cemeterykeys001","name":"Lorenzo's Cemetery Keys","type":"object","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Complete set of keys to open hatches accessing underground pit in Cemetery of the Innocents. Held by Lorenzo Scannapecore, Italian plague doctor hired by Paris to manage excessive corpses in mass graves. Keys open large reinforced trap doors leading to huge pit where bodies of those who cannot afford burial are thrown. Underground pit contains crowds of restless spirits invisible to mundane eyes, accumulating spiritual energy from passage of comet Morituris. Lorenzo sent cemetery keepers away to secretly host Alizée, fugitive nun he loves.","quantity":1,"weight":1,"value":50,"equipped":false,"properties":["Opens cemetery hatches","Access to underground pit","Held by Lorenzo","Mass grave entry","Spirit-filled location"],"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"cometmorituris001","name":"The Comet Morituris","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Long-tailed comet passing over Paris on December 31st, bright as small sun at midnight. According to legend, passage gives power to spirits and charges spiritual world with energy. Name 'Morituris' means 'those who are about to die' in Latin. Comet's passage allows Yvonne to channel mystical energy of unquiet dead souls into inferno capable of burning all Paris. Visible from sky during stroke of midnight. Adds 1 Grudge Token to underground pit at midnight. Lorenzo Scannapecore is skilled astrologer who can explain comet's spiritual significance and timing.","location":"Sky over Paris, visible December 31st at midnight","importance":"crucial","found":false,"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"ravenshideout001","name":"The Ravens' Hideout Evidence","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Part of catacombs frequented only by scoundrels who had business with Adrien. Couple of broken absinthe bottles scattered among makeshift beds with strong alcohol scent still present. Old dagger and wooden crucifix are only other noteworthy details. Ravens are young arrogant smugglers who distribute Adrien's illegal absinthe. They boasted about profits made from important customer (Father Adrien) who can provide goods defying any authority. Olivier the Raven prepares his escape here before sunset, or his charred corpse found after nightfall. Evidence links smuggling operation directly to church.","location":"East side of the catacombs","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"yvonnebedding001","name":"Yvonne's Alcove with Withered Flowers","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Small stone alcove in catacombs with bed of straw and rags where foundling Yvonne slept. Old vase of withered flowers indicates no one has used it for more than week. Poor old woman Marie can tell Hunters that foundling named Yvonne slept here. Girl hasn't been back for over week since her murder. Alcove represents Yvonne's meager living conditions - ragged orphan who sold candles to survive, scorned by all except Father Adrien. Location where Yvonne's spirit returns during day, sadly absorbed in memory of her death. Withered flowers perhaps left by someone who cared.","location":"The Catacombs of Paris - Yvonne's sleeping alcove","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"yvonneteeth001","name":"Yvonne's Shining White Teeth","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Only intact part of Yvonne's charred body after Father Adrien burned her alive. Small corpse found with teeth shining white and locked in deathly grin - horrifying smile frozen in death. This macabre detail is what identified the body as Yvonne. The 'smile in the darkness' that gives scenario its name. Teeth remained pristine white despite fire that consumed rest of body. Many poor people who depend on Adrien witnessed scene but kept quiet to not lose priest's favor. Body thrown into mass grave without ceremony before Yvonne reborn as vengeful spirit.","location":"Yvonne's charred remains in catacombs","importance":"crucial","found":true,"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
{"_id":"yvonnecandle001","name":"Yvonne's Untouched Candle","type":"clue","img":"systems/brokentales/styles/icons/icon_gift.webp","system":{"description":"Small candle miraculously untouched by flames, found under ashes where little Yvonne's charred body was discovered. Yvonne was ragged orphan who sold candles to survive on Paris streets. This candle survived the fire that killed her when Father Adrien strangled and burned her to hide his absinthe smuggling secret. Represents Yvonne's innocent profession and tragic end. Found scattered in various tunnels where burned-alive victims' bodies were discovered.","location":"The Burns - scattered patches of ash in catacombs tunnels","importance":"important","found":false,"scenario":"the-smile-in-the-darkness"},"flags":{},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0}}
